      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cfd-hemolysis-worst-case",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for FDA generic centrifugal blood pump",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, employing the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage model with SST k-omega turbulence closure, correctly ranks the relative hemolysis index (RH) across all five flow-speed operating points. The model predicts that the 2.5 L/min, 3600 RPM condition produces peak RH values exceeding those of the predicate device, constituting the worst-case scenario for regulatory submission. This claim encompasses geometric fidelity of the FDA generic pump, boundary condition representativeness, and mesh-independence of shear stress predictions in the impeller gap region.",
      "purpose": "Support regulatory decision that CFD simulation results are sufficient to identify worst-case hemolysis conditions without exhaustive physical testing of all operating points.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; Class II CPB indication; five operating points (2.5–6 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM); relative hemolysis index as primary QoI."
    }
  ],
